trization. The case is made that reaction-induced $l$ dependence is a\ngeneral property of nucleon-nucleus and nucleus-nucleus interactions and\nrepresents a valid extension of the nuclear optical model.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 5 Feb 2013 16:28:38 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 3 Jul 2015 16:17:57 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 18 Aug 2015 12:59:31 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Sat, 19 Mar 2016 17:05:41 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Fri, 16 Dec 2016 14:27:02 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Thu, 14 Mar 2019 16:39:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-03-15"}
